{
  "texts": [
    "the data referred to as a Stokes shell by in [Moc25]).",
    "• For each active exponent ⟨f ⟩ the (⟨f ⟩-graded) local system V 0 ⟨f ⟩ on ∂.",
    "It can be viewed as a local system on ⟨f ⟩, and is hence given by the following data: for any I ∈ A(f), the vector space K f I:= (V 0 ⟨f ⟩) m I ∼ = Γ(I, V 0 ⟨f ⟩), and for any two adjacent intervals I, J ∈ A(f), J following I with respect to the given orientation, an isomorphism",
    "• for each Stokes arrow, the corresponding deformation datum R p q, as in Definition 4.9.",
    "This observation follows, for example, from the fact that the notion of Stokes shell is equivalent to that of a Stokes-filtered local system and hence to that of a Stokes local system (combining [Moc25, Proposition 3.4.3] and [Boa21, §9 and Theorem 11.3])."
  ]
}